Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.00,0:00:02.65,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's almost the tenth anniversary of Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.65,0:00:04.47,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}We made it through the first, now let's aim for the next!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.47,0:00:06.30,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}After all, the {\i1}butsumetsu{\i0} calendar bugs me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.30,0:00:07.95,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Psychic phenomena brought on by a nightmare!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.95,0:00:09.95,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Passing through security, a case breaks out!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.95,0:00:11.48,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.48,0:00:13.22,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.22,0:00:15.20,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.34,0:01:53.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,An evil spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.91,0:01:56.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You want me to break the curse of an evil spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.76,0:01:59.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well... To put it simply, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.51,0:02:04.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on! Detectives solve crimes! Human crimes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.42,0:02:11.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We've already had priests and mediums in\Nto get rid of the spirit, but no luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.49,0:02:14.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we decided to ask you, Detective Mouri,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.55,0:02:19.05,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenzo Akatsuka (50)\NKunitomo Family Butler
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.55,0:02:19.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to investigate from a scientific standpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.50,0:02:22.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So what's this spook doing, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.15,0:02:26.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It all started with a nightmare my master had two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.49,0:02:28.34,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Nightmare?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.34,0:02:31.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He gave an unearthly scream and jumped out of bed,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.54,0:02:37.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,moaning the same things over and over... "It's a curse... I'm going to be killed..."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.05,0:02:39.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was just a dream, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.75,0:02:42.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not all!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.75,0:02:50.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Six months later, the brakes of this car malfunctioned and we almost crashed!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.71,0:02:53.96,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Masashi Watabiki (28)\NKunitomo Family Chauffeur
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.06,0:02:52.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.81,0:02:53.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Er, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.43,0:02:59.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry about that. I didn't notice the brake oil had leaked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.62,0:03:03.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The accident was such a shock to the master\Nthat he started having heart problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.78,0:03:07.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His eyes sunk into their sockets\Nand his hair turned white.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.13,0:03:12.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But still, that's just an accident.\NWhere does the evil spirit come in?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.88,0:03:15.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We have reason to believe we've been cursed!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.87,0:03:18.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We received this card!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.84,0:03:20.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Card?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.13,0:03:24.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Repent of your sins before I awaken."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.58,0:03:27.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"I am the fifth soul."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.32,0:03:37.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When did you get this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.57,0:03:39.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Last year, not long after New Year's Day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.64,0:03:41.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It had been left in the mailbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.28,0:03:45.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At first I thought it was just a prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.62,0:03:47.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But when I showed it to the master,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.00,0:03:50.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,both he and the mistress were horrified.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.62,0:03:52.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.09,0:03:53.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.05,0:03:57.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Six months later, a cupboard fell,\Nshattering all the fine china inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.93,0:04:02.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And this April the staff went on vacation, leaving the master and mistress alone in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.57,0:04:04.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They started hearing strange sounds...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.34,0:04:08.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, do these weird things\Nhappen on a certain day?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.20,0:04:12.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Like Friday the 13th or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.17,0:04:16.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They've happened on different days of the week. But the date...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.96,0:04:18.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,is always the 4th.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.32,0:04:22.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe something significant happened\Non the 4th of some month in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.49,0:04:26.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked the master, the mistress and the staff,\Nbut they couldn't think of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.97,0:04:28.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.36,0:04:33.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Today is October 3!\NThe curse is going to strike tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.01,0:04:35.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.04,0:04:38.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.74,0:04:41.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There have been five incidents, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.78,0:04:44.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember the exact dates they occurred on?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.35,0:04:47.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't recall every detail...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.19,0:04:48.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.52,0:04:53.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The first incident was...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.76,0:04:57.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,two years ago on February 4.\NThat was the master's nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.86,0:05:00.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The car accident occurred\Non July 4 of the same year.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.99,0:05:04.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We received the strange card\Nlast year on February 4,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.97,0:05:08.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the cupboard fell down on July 4 of that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.78,0:05:12.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the mysterious sounds\Nwere heard this April 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.25,0:05:16.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You make a note of everything, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.34,0:05:19.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... If I don't write things down, I'll forget them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.53,0:05:21.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like you, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.98,0:05:23.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.64,0:05:33.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the card was sent by someone trying to get to your boss...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.40,0:05:37.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, do you feel anything from it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.02,0:05:40.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? You mean like a psychic vibe?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.32,0:05:41.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, er...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.75,0:05:45.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't feel anything, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.20,0:05:50.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.38,0:05:52.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't what I was told!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.21,0:05:54.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we were only going to have\None guest at the house tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.67,0:05:56.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Er, I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.95,0:06:00.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My daughter pestered me to let her tag along.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.23,0:06:01.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.80,0:06:08.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not angry at you! I'm annoyed\Nat this silly old man for not calling me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.25,0:06:11.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Namika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, please... I'm not that old.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.58,0:06:13.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'll have to go get more groceries.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.17,0:06:17.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's a pretty outspoken daughter, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.26,0:06:19.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no... She's our chef.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.72,0:06:20.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Chef?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.88,0:06:27.17,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Namika Senzaki (28)\NKunitomo Family Chef
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.95,0:06:25.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Her father was the Kunitomo family's personal chef for years,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.99,0:06:29.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and after he died in an accident, she took his place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.77,0:06:32.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... And she's still so young...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.60,0:06:36.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which, {\i1}he{\i0} followed in his father's footsteps too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.95,0:06:43.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! The master has an appointment at the hospital at 8:00 tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.51,0:06:44.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.45,0:06:46.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.05,0:06:49.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm out of ink.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.64,0:06:50.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.06,0:06:53.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Use this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.60,0:06:55.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.30,0:07:04.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. No hard feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.25,0:07:09.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had food poisoning when I was small,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.75,0:07:12.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and ever since, I've suffered from mysophobia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.37,0:07:14.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.54,0:07:21.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! We'll go in without you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.96,0:07:24.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave him, leave him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.62,0:07:27.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? The master and mistress?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.66,0:07:31.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw them in the bedroom on the third floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.27,0:07:32.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.17,0:07:34.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.38,0:07:35.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.37,0:07:38.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You look a lot like that chef I just saw...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.31,0:07:41.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.25,0:07:46.21,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Shigeko Senzaki (52)\NKunitomo Family Housekeeper
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.25,0:07:43.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.49,0:07:46.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Namika is my daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.21,0:07:48.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.56,0:07:53.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And could you not point your finger at me? I have belonephobia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.79,0:07:55.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.30,0:07:58.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Belonephobia...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.70,0:08:00.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.13,0:08:05.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You want me to deliver a message to the master?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.50,0:08:08.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'll see him in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.73,0:08:14.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Shigeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Ncould you fix that painting for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.35,0:08:19.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about 5 mm off to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.49,0:08:24.80,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}5 mm?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.94,0:08:27.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.70,0:08:29.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.15,0:08:31.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.90,0:08:45.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a strange place to have a door.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.72,0:08:53.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... A friend of the mistress installed this after that strange card arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.30,0:08:55.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's quite something!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.57,0:09:00.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You type in the PIN,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.35,0:09:02.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and place your index finger here...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.78,0:09:09.68,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.25,0:09:12.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuka, the butler.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.43,0:09:15.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've brought Detective Mouri with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.30,0:09:17.34,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ah... I'll open the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.94,0:09:21.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Like so!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.53,0:09:23.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.83,0:09:26.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The doorbell won't ring until the machine has registered
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.95,0:09:30.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,a fingerprint from a member of the household.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.72,0:09:32.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like sci-fi!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.84,0:09:35.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.16,0:09:42.37,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Yasue Kunitomo (42)\NWife of the Head of the Kunitomo Family
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.36,0:09:42.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,These days, some apartments have fingerprint authentication systems too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.20,0:09:46.41,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Toshimichi Sekiguchi (43)\NSecurity Company President
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.39,0:09:46.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It just hasn't caught on with the public yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.78,0:09:50.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Yasue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}, the mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.21,0:09:56.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The man on the left is her friend Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}, who installed that door.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.00,0:09:59.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody opened the door for us this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.57,0:10:03.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but what if nobody is on the third floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.06,0:10:08.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it can't be opened\Nby anyone but my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.21,0:10:13.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the members of the household can leave this floor by entering their fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.95,0:10:16.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if somebody else sticks a finger in?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.74,0:10:18.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.42,0:10:22.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If the system doesn't recognize a fingerprint,\Nall the alarms in the house will go off
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.85,0:10:25.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the security company will dispatch guards here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.80,0:10:27.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oopsie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.01,0:10:30.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to install surveillance cameras too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.13,0:10:32.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I turned him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.46,0:10:35.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm okay with having one at the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.09,0:10:40.64,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Atsuhiro Kunitomo (56)\NHead of the Kunitomo Family
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.53,0:10:42.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't want to cover this fine house my father designed with ugly machinery.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.58,0:10:45.38,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Their security's already over the top...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.72,0:10:49.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you must be Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the great detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.27,0:10:50.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.43,0:10:55.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Kunitomo. I'm the one who invited you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.92,0:10:59.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you can get to the bottom of this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.63,0:11:00.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Er, sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.30,0:11:08.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, if you would like,\NI'll show you around the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.80,0:11:09.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, why not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.21,0:11:15.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, kid, hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.19,0:11:16.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.99,0:11:25.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it safe to have a detective snooping around?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.51,0:11:28.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if he finds out about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.08,0:11:30.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.69,0:11:33.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The evidence is long gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.57,0:11:36.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But judging from what was written on that card...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.40,0:11:39.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I hired a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.09,0:11:42.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to catch the person who's threatening me
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.20,0:11:44.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and find out how much they know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.22,0:11:49.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on! I'll get your medicine!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.09,0:11:53.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your medicine...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.13,0:12:00.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.68,0:12:04.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, you're gonna kick the bucket\Nbefore we capture this guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.43,0:12:06.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch how you talk to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.66,0:12:09.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is all your fault to begin with!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.49,0:12:12.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I came down here for!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.07,0:12:13.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's tomorrow, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.50,0:12:15.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The big day...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.00,0:12:16.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.25,0:12:20.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The rat hiding in my walls will scurry out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.00,0:12:45.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.66,0:12:47.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.94,0:12:52.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do I think? It's delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.03,0:12:55.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not the food! The investigation!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.95,0:13:00.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't say anything yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.09,0:13:09.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If somebody tampered with the cupboard and created those sounds,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.09,0:13:11.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,they've probably gotten rid of the evidence by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.50,0:13:15.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You're wearing gloves at the table again!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.07,0:13:17.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wash everything, you know! How rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.34,0:13:18.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.94,0:13:22.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I have to take the master to the hospital soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.90,0:13:23.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.86,0:13:26.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, have some coffee before you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.55,0:13:33.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Those two seem close.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.76,0:13:37.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Their parents were friends. They've known each other since they were children.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.59,0:13:40.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Chef, can I have some coffee too?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.40,0:13:41.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.13,0:13:48.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, I'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.63,0:13:51.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.00,0:13:56.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She has acrophobia. Can't get close to any window that's higher than the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.33,0:14:04.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the butler is a perfectionist who can't stand to have things the tiniest bit out of line!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.61,0:14:08.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A crooked tablecloth drives him crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.07,0:14:11.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.79,0:14:13.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.54,0:14:15.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with this house?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.04,0:14:18.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mysophobia—fear of germs. Belonephobia—fear of sharp objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.85,0:14:22.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Acrophobia—fear of heights. And a butler with OCD.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.23,0:14:30.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I took this job so I could get a taste of the high life at a millionaire's mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.45,0:14:34.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If I'd known there were ghosts involved, I'd have stayed home with Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.24,0:14:36.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what are you looking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.34,0:14:41.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The dates of the five spooky incidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.56,0:14:46.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Two years ago, there were events on February 4 and July 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.45,0:14:49.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Same thing last year—February 4 and July 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.22,0:14:51.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the first incident this year was on April 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.06,0:14:54.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think it happened in April this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.37,0:14:55.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.50,0:14:58.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the 5th is usually a busy day, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.95,0:15:01.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad was out on February 5 and July 5\Nlast year and the year before...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.88,0:15:07.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You went to weddings, helped people move and went on neighborhood association trips!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.97,0:15:12.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, I want to a wedding on April 5 this year too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.05,0:15:17.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, people usually choose to do weddings,\Ntrips and moves on {\i1}taian{\i0} days, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.19,0:15:18.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.75,0:15:20.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.05,0:15:22.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the day before a lucky {\i1}taian{\i0} day
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.02,0:15:24.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,is always a {\i1}butsumetsu{\i0}—the unluckiest day!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.40,0:15:26.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-{\i1}Butsumetsu{\i0}, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.70,0:15:28.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.11,0:15:32.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a poster up in our neighborhood\Nabout a supermarket re-opening on October 5!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.85,0:15:34.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And your point is?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.32,0:15:38.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then October 4 is a {\i1}butsumetsu{\i0} day! Are you saying something will happen tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.38,0:15:40.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Today! It's already the 4th!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.93,0:15:46.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What was that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.16,0:15:52.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A shoe?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.37,0:16:22.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Akatsuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}? It's me, Yasue.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.21,0:16:25.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We had a flat tire and took some time replacing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.40,0:16:28.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry we're running late, but we'll be back shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.65,0:16:31.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.96,0:16:33.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.45,0:16:34.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.62,0:16:38.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,From the balcony of the upstairs bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.00,0:16:40.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've called for an ambulance and the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.56,0:16:45.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but the master is the only one who can get into the third floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.34,0:16:46.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please hurry back...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.17,0:16:50.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.60,0:16:52.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the curse...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.45,0:16:53.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,An evil spirit...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.71,0:16:55.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Darling!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.50,0:17:00.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your medicine!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.87,0:17:03.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.76,0:17:06.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.50,0:17:15.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The deceased is Toshimichi Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, age 41.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.99,0:17:21.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Estimated time of death is approximately four hours ago, around 8:30 to 9:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.92,0:17:27.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been told Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was a friend of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.10,0:17:30.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ever since high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.80,0:17:33.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He ran a security company.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.67,0:17:38.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he the one who installed the fingerprint authentication system
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.56,0:17:39.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,on the door to the third floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.90,0:17:40.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.81,0:17:46.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And where were you two at the time of his death?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.60,0:17:50.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband and I were in our car\Non the way to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.00,0:17:54.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband has heart problems,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.80,0:17:58.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so he visits a doctor for a checkup on the 3rd of every month.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.39,0:18:00.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When did you leave the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.20,0:18:02.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Around 8:00, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.19,0:18:05.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think {\i1}we{\i0} killed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.09,0:18:11.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The master and mistress had most certainly left the house by 8:00 PM!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.37,0:18:13.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.51,0:18:20.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I came up to the third floor at 7:45 PM sharp to take them down to the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.93,0:18:25.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} was definitely alive at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.05,0:18:28.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.12,0:18:33.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, he committed suicide, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.40,0:18:36.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... This is a bit strange for a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.14,0:18:41.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The noose around his neck...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.00,0:18:43.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,is unusually close to the balcony railing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.31,0:18:48.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not impossible, mind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.38,0:18:54.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to suspect that this is a murder\Nset up to look like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.32,0:18:58.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if it's suicide or murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.24,0:19:02.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But this card, "Here I pay for my sins from 13 years ago",
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.45,0:19:05.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,may be the key to the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.50,0:19:07.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.45,0:19:09.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you find that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.90,0:19:14.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We found it on Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s person before the cops arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.11,0:19:17.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You interfered with the crime scene\Nbefore we could examine it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.71,0:19:20.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. I gave him a good wallop for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.04,0:19:24.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.98,0:19:27.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But what does the card mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.16,0:19:30.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"My sins from 13 years ago"...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.14,0:19:33.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dunno. It looks like some kind of suicide note...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.35,0:19:34.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I bet the three people behind me,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.95,0:19:37.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,whose faces turned pale after seeing the card,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.40,0:19:40.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,can fill us in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.95,0:19:44.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.58,0:19:47.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember something that happened thirteen years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.95,0:19:51.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thirteen years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.35,0:19:56.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The master's cruiser{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} san{\r}k into the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.35,0:19:57.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.72,0:19:58.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.88,0:20:07.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Back then, the whole household\Nused to go out on an annual cruise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.02,0:20:09.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The cruiser was shipwrecked off the coast of Suruga Bay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.94,0:20:13.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The master, mistress and Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r},\Nwho was there as their guest,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.54,0:20:15.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,somehow managed to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.85,0:20:18.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What about anyone else on the ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.73,0:20:22.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone else on board was lost,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.14,0:20:25.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the cruiser itself was never recovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.08,0:20:30.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then maybe Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} caused the accident
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.07,0:20:32.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and someone had a grudge against him for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.92,0:20:33.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.90,0:20:38.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never been fond of the sea,\Nso I never attended those cruises.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.21,0:20:41.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the two survivors\Nknow what happened, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.87,0:20:46.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,About why the ship{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} san{\r}k.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.00,0:20:47.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.21,0:20:51.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was taking a nap inside the ship when Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} suddenly told us to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.06,0:20:53.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In the chaos, we never found out what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.57,0:21:00.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say... Did the people who died in that accident leave any family here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.25,0:21:01.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.86,0:21:03.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.31,0:21:08.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,this may have something to do with the five strange incidents in this house...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.86,0:21:09.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Five incidents?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.86,0:21:12.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I was hired to investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.89,0:21:17.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The master had a nightmare, the car almost crashed because the brakes malfunctioned,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.53,0:21:24.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,a cupboard fell in the middle of the night, and strange sounds were heard inside the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.12,0:21:28.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And last but not least...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.15,0:21:31.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The family received this card.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.95,0:21:34.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.58,0:21:39.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks just like the card found on Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.58,0:21:44.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And all five incidents happened on an unlucky {\i1}butsumetsu{\i0} day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.01,0:21:48.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only natural to suspect an inside job, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.70,0:21:50.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.92,0:21:56.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You suspect one of the shipwreck victims has a relative working here,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.99,0:22:01.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,who blamed Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} for the accident and decided to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.16,0:22:07.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please call for anyone who fits that description!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.45,0:22:09.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.75,0:22:12.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s wristwatch...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.78,0:22:14.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's something carved on the dial plate!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.75,0:22:17.48,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"E" and "N"?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.23,0:22:20.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Usually when you see "E" and "N"...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.50,0:22:22.62,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Fingerprints?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.85,0:22:24.53,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That means...!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.07,0:23:59.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That...can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.62,0:24:02.13,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And that rope bugs me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.85,0:24:04.77,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If my deduction is correct...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.09,0:24:07.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.50,0:24:09.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's a curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.84,0:24:12.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The master must've seen that ghost!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.57,0:24:15.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm warning you! Open this door right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.09,0:24:19.08,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Intruder alert!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.08,0:24:25.05,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.42,0:24:30.05,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.42,0:24:30.05,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Fingerprints
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.13,0:24:31.48,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, show me your fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.48,0:24:31.77,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.77,0:24:33.37,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, these fingerprints are Shin'ichi's?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.66,0:24:34.44,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you surprised?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.44,0:24:34.87,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
